{
  "stem": "13382.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was-- they tried to send me to-- to learn some trade somewhere, but wherever I went, I felt uncomfortable.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And either justifiably or not, I always complained about my stomach.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] And so when I said my stomach is hurting-- then come home, my son.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] And Frank was, of course, at home, because he--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Frank was-- well, Frank went to school and was at home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was still a little kid.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now the war came in stages, right?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a-- I mean, physically, our war really started in 1944.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, the rest really-- we just sort of gathered information from radio.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The pressure was on-- on us Jews, because the more the Nazis and-- was--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--developing and-- and the more the anti-Semitism started-- sort of grew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we felt it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, either-- either they didn't show it or not, it was in the air.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we felt very, very insecure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, we-- we know all right till about 1940.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I just so really like to remind you something.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The biggest shock in our life came in 1940 or '41.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I don't remember exactly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As my mother family-- part of the family-- was cut off from us-- was in Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the new regime in Slovakia-- I mean, it was a fascist regime.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH], and all the thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think they made a pact with Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I just-- we found out now-- that Germany was buying Jewish stores or Jewish heads [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think 2/3 of the Jewish people in Slovakia were deported.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And with them, my mother's two brothers-- married brothers with four children and an unmarried brother-- they were taken away, and we never heard of them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That was, say, in '41.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
